/**
 * The Faheem brand mark. Geometry is TRACED (potrace) from the 2026-07 Canva
 * brand refresh; the source bitmaps and their traced SVGs are vendored in
 * context/branding/logo-src/. The glyph is colour-separated into the three navy
 * shapes (two bars + the up-arrow) plus the emerald check that sweeps beneath
 * them, so the shapes can animate independently. Fills resolve to theme tokens
 * (`brand`) or to `currentColor` (`mono`, e.g. the login watermark); the source
 * colours ARE the brand tokens, so no hex is ever baked in.
 *
 * `animated` staggers the three navy shapes then sweeps the emerald check in
 * last (≤400ms, reduced-motion safe), used on login and as the chat "thinking"
 * affordance.
 *
 * The wordmark ("faheem" / فهيم) is now TRACED art, not a font: the brand draws
 * the "ee" as round eyeglasses, so each wordmark is drawn geometry rather than
 * type. Both are inlined here as their own SVGs, navy / tone-aware like the
 * glyph, and rely on `fillRule="evenodd"` so the lenses, specular highlights,
 * and letter counters render as holes rather than filling solid.
 */

